25|$|In later, secular times, the <b>bell</b> <b>ringer</b> {{would pass}} {{through the streets of}} villages, towns or cities announcing the name of a {{recently}} deceased person, with details of the funeral. At the funeral the <b>bell</b> <b>ringer,</b> often the beadle, would walk at the head the cortege, solemnly ringing the bell from the home of the deceased until the church was reached. The bell was also sometimes used to indicate {{the point at which the}} coffin-bearers were changed.|$|E
